TEXT(beginproblem());

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
The solution of the equation
\[\sqrt[3]{2x-1} -3 = 0 \]
is \(x=\)  \{ ans_rule(4) \}.
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(14));





TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BR Hint: You can eliminate the cube root by isolating it and cubing both sides (raising both sides to the power 3).
EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
We isolate the radical and remove it by cubing:
\[
\begin{array}{rclcl}
(2x-1)^{\frac{1}{3}} -3 &=& 0 &|& +3 \\
(2x-1)^{\frac{1}{3}}  &=& 3 &|& ()^3 \\
2x-1 &=& 27 &|& + 1 \\
2x &=& 28 &|& \div 2 \\
x &=& 14 &|& \hbox{the answer} \\
\end{array}
\]
EOT






